# Hard-mask full systemd so it can NEVER be silently pulled in as PID 1.
#
# OxysOS is OpenRC-only. USE="-systemd elogind" (make.conf + livecd/use) stops
# packages from *enabling* their systemd integration, but it does NOT stop a
# package from pulling sys-apps/systemd through an unconditional dependency or a
# `|| ( sys-apps/systemd sys-apps/systemd-utils[...] )` any-of block. When that
# happens systemd merges, seizes /sbin/init, and the ISO (and every target
# rsync'd from it) boots systemd instead of OpenRC -- exactly the "still picked
# up systemd" symptom, with no obvious cause in the USE flags.
#
# Masking sys-apps/systemd converts that silent capture into a BUILD FAILURE that
# names the offending package ("masked by: package.mask ... required by <pkg>"),
# so the real puller is visible instead of shipping in the image. udev/tmpfiles
# come from sys-apps/systemd-utils (left unmasked), which never provides the PID 1
# manager binary. If the failure points at a `[...kernel-install]`-style any-of,
# enable that flag on systemd-utils rather than unmasking systemd.
#
# To temporarily allow a systemd build (e.g. init_system: Systemd), delete this
# file.
sys-apps/systemd
